            "answer_text": "Did the South divide into two camps during the Civil War? The reality is they could not divide into two camps. It was already every state for themselves. The Confederacy was a rejection of the Constitution of the United States and a return to the old Articles of Confederation. An example: Many soldiers in the Army of Northern Virginia were freezing wearing rags of uniforms while marching without any boots. Meanwhile there were thousands of uniforms and boots stockpiled in North Carolina warehouses. For the use of North Carolinian soldiers not for Confederate Soldiers. This inherent division was only one of the many reasons the CSA were doomed from the beginning of the war they started. ",
